  "text": "The in vitro gas production technique has the potential to reflect the in vivo digestibility of feeds for ruminants; the highest predictive value for the in vivo digestibility of straw was obtained after 45 to 52 h of in vitro fermentation [CITATION_1] . When proportionality between gas production after 48 h of incubation and digestibility is assumed, the treatments with NaOH, urea, and (NH 4 )HCO 3 increased the digestibility of rice straw by 55, 52, and 37%, respectively (Table 3).",
